          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="agm"></a>The Sanderstead Residents' Association AGM, Thursday 28th April 2016 at 8pm</h3>
              <p>The Sanderstead Residents' Association AGM will be held on Thursday 28th April, in All Saints' Church Hall, Onslow Gardens, Sanderstead, CR2 9AB.The AGM is your meeting when you have the opportunity to question your Committee, Councillors and possibly your MP. We will report on our finances and our various activities. Please bring along ideas about whom you consider we should be supporting with grants and the future direction of the Sanderstead Residents Association.</p></td>
            <td class="events"><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/residents_logo100.jpg", alt: "SRA logo"), "http://www.sanderstead-residents.co.uk" %></td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="mariona2"></a>Guided Walk in King's Wood, Friday 29th April, 10 am</h3>
              <p>(GR 349 603) Enjoy the freshness of new leaves on our native trees above and delicate flowers at our feet. A gentle two hour amble starting from where Orchard Road enters woodland (off Limpsfield Road, Sanderstead, B269). Volunteer Marion's walks explore local countryside, wildlife and history. Boots are advised as paths may be muddy, and waterproofs in case of rain. Dogs allowed if on leads. Finish at the start point. Walks are free.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to("Marion's Walks", "/resource/marion.pdf")%></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td>
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="tennis"></a>Sanderstead Lawn Tennis Club, Penwortham Road, Charity Day and Tournament. Bank Holiday Monday 2nd May</h3>
              <p>SLTC is holding its annual charity day at the club on Mayday Bank Holiday Monday 2nd May from 11 00. In addition to a tennis tournament there will be stalls selling a variety of products, a midday Bar-B-Q serving traditional hot food and the bar will be open all day.</p>

              <p>In past years this annual event has raised thousands of pounds for local charities and this year’s charity is The Purley Cancer Centre. All visitors are welcome. Website <%= link_to "www.sandersteadltc.co.uk", "http://www.sandersteadltc.co.uk" %></p>
            </td>
            <td><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/tennis_club.gif", alt: "tennis club logo"), "http://sandersteadltc.co.uk" %>
              </td>
            </tr>


          <tr>
            <td>
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="parlour"></a>Parlour Players present "The Bard Unbuttonded". 12 - 14 May 2016</h3>
              <p>Parlour Players Spring Production, 12th – 14th May 2016 at Sanderstead URC is titled ‘The Bard Unbuttoned’ an acknowledgement of William Shakespeare in the 400th year of the anniversary of his death. There are two plays with  Shakespearian themes – ‘Don’t Blame it on the Boots’ and ‘The Droitwich Discovery’. Evening performances commence at 7.45 pm on each night, there is a licenced bar for pre-performance and interval drinks and tea and coffee is also available. Please put the date in your diary and box office details will be added shortly.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events"><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/parlour_players.jpg", alt: "Parlour Players logo"), "http://www.parlourplayers.co.uk/" %>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="water"></a>Sutton and East Surrey Water Company, Customer Open Day, Saturday 14th May 2016</h3>
              <p>Sutton and East Surrey Water’s Bough Beech Reservoir and Water Treatment Works. From Source to Tap – Free Customer Open Day - Saturday 14 May 2016 9.30am - 12.00pm or 1.00pm – 3.30pm</p>

              <p>Sutton and East Surrey Water supplies around 160 million litres of water a day to 685,000 people and 17,000 businesses in East Surrey, parts of West Sussex, West Kent and South London. Groundwater supplies provide 85 per cent and the remaining 15 per cent comes from our only surface reservoir at Bough Beech. </p>

              <p>Come and take a look behind the scenes to see how water is treated from ‘source to tap’ to produce your high quality drinking water. </p>

              <p>As this is an operational plant and the behind-the-scenes tour incorporates metal stairs and walkways, regrettably we are unable to accommodate people with impaired mobility or children under 14 years of age. ID will be required. This event is only open to Sutton and East Surrey Water customers and booking is essential.</p>

              <p>To book your free place, please contact 01732 375417 (Monday to Friday, 9.00am-5.00pm).    <%= link_to "www.waterplc.com", "http://www.waterplc.com" %>.<p>
            </td>
            <td classs="events"><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/sutton_water.png", alt: "water logo"), "http://www.waterplc.com" %>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="hearme"></a>Hear Me Speak, debating competition for Primary Schools. Thursday 9th June, 3.15 - 4 pm</h3>
              <p>The third year of our popular debating competition for year 6 children is to be held at Hamsey Green Primary School. For more information please contact Cliff Quartly <%= mail_to "francisquartly@hotmail.co.uk" %></p>
            </td>
            <td class="events"><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/residents_logo100.jpg", alt: "SRA logo"), "http://www.sanderstead-residents.co.uk" %>
