          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="festival"></a>Sanderstead Festival of Music and Dance, Saturday 18th June 2016</h3>
              <p>A new venture for Sanderstead Community, a music and dance festival will be held on Saturday 18th June, 2-6 pm. Sponsored by our local Councillors, the Residents' Association, All Saints' Church and Priscilla's, it will be held on the Gruffy, in All Saints' Halls and All Saints' Church. We are already booking some exciting acts, and if you would like to be involved please contact Dennis King tel: 020 8657 2661, <%= mail_to "chairman@sanderstead-residents.co.uk" %> View our flyers here.</p>
              <p><%= link_to("Sanderstead Festival page 1", "resource/Flyer_Page_1.pdf") %></p>
              <p><%= link_to("Sanderstead Festival page 2", "resource/Flyer_Page_2.pdf") %></p>
            </td>
            <td class="events"><%= link_to image_tag("Festival_image.jpg", alt: "Festival logo"), "resource/Flyer_Page_1.pdf" %>
            </td>
          </tr>




          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="band"></a>Our Kind of Swing, featuring the Big Band Sound of The Nigel Garrard Orchestra on Saturday 18th June at 8 pm</h3>
              <p>Enjoy the music of Glenn Miller, Count Basie and Ted Heath. Join us on Saturday 18th June at All Saints’ Church Halls, Onslow Gardens, Sanderstead CR2 9AB.</p>
              <p>Concert starts at 8.00pm. Doors open at 7.30pm. Tickets £15 (Children under 15 - £12). BOX OFFICE TELEPHONE 0208 657 2624. All profits will go to local charities and good causes. <%= link_to("Application form for tickets", "resource/swing_flyer.pdf") %>.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events"><h3><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/trombones100.jpg", alt: "Swing Band"), "resource/swing_flyer.pdf" %></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">       
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="surc"></a>Sunday afternoon Concerts at SURC</h3>
              <p>The next concert in the SURC concert series is a concert of contrasts on Sunday 19th June. The concerts start at 3 pm and last around an hour, followed by tea, coffee and cakes which are included in the price of £7 and £3 (under 18).</p>
              <ul>
                <li><b>19th June</b> A concert of contrasts with trumpet, organ and harp</li>
                <li><b>24th July</b> Surrey Harmony with their lively ladies' barbershop</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For more information contact: <%= mail_to "sanderstead.music@gmail.com" %>, <%= link_to "www.surc.org.uk", "http://www.surc.org.uk" %> or telephone 07563 917777</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/surc.jpg", alt: "SURC logo"), "http://www.surc.org.uk" %>
            </td>
          </tr>


           <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="marionj"></a>Guided Walk on Farthing Downs, Saturday 24th June, 10 am</h3>
              <p>(GR 302 572) See what flowers are now flourishing on slopes where scrub has been removed. Some longish slopes on this easy paced two hour walk exploring a spectular chalk valley. Leave fom Farthing Downs car park, one mile south of Coulsdon South station. Volunteer Marion's walks explore local countryside, wildlife and history. Boots are advised as paths may be muddy, and waterproofs in case of rain. Dogs allowed if on leads. Finish at the start point. Walks are free.</p>
            </td>
